  "summary": "Malicious code in type-slint (npm)",
  "details": "Type-slint@3.3.7 is a combosquat of the pino logging library. On require, it spawns a detached background process that fetches arbitrary JavaScript from an IPFS gateway and executes it via the Function constructor, giving the attacker full remote code execution on the installer's machine. The second-stage payload is fetched from hxxps://bronze-improved-gibbon-411[.]mypinata[.]cloud/ipfs/bafkreigjnxn5vnn34rc5r43ajwwkmk4akqpm4awmq5gdhakgszpeqiffsu. No token or credential theft was observed in the first-stage code, but the dynamic payload can perform any action.",
